s in exchange rate policy and international business prospects. The second section addresses banking and financial markets, tracking the reforms to date and establishing the need for upgraded technology. The final section compares India's fiscal performance with that of other developing countries, highlighting worrying trends, and presents concrete policy recommendations to advance Indian reforms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aAsian Studies. 4aEconomics -- Economic Policy. 4aEconomics -- Microeconomics and Macroeconomics. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Macroeconomics.2bisacsh1 aAuerbach, Alan J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChinoy, Sajjid Z., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChinoy, Sajjid Z., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEcheverri-Gent, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanson, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarberger, Arnold C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamath, K. V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrueger, Anne O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrueger, Anne O., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNarain, Ravi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRajan, Raghuram G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShah, Ajay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingh, N. K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSrinivasan, T. N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/